  "prompt": "How many people get hire by Google onsite interview?",
  "response": "The number of people hired by Google after an onsite interview can vary and is not publicly disclosed in precise figures. However, Google's hiring process is known to be highly selective. Typically, only a small percentage of candidates who reach the onsite interview stage are extended job offers. It's estimated that Google makes offers to about 20-30% of candidates at the onsite interview stage, but these figures can vary based on the role, location, and the specific needs of the company at any given time.\n\nFor the most accurate and current information, it would be best to refer to Google's recruitment data or speak directly with a recruiter at Google.",
